{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id5fff70ea-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s351"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"351"},"text":"§ 351.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"As used in this chapter “United States” includes Alaska. “Acquired lands” or “lands acquired by the United States” include all lands heretofore or hereafter acquired by the United States to which the “mineral leasing laws” have not been extended, including such lands acquired under the provisions of the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1911-03-01"},"text":"March 1, 1911","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/961"},"text":"36 Stat. 961","children":[],"tail":", 16 U.S.C., sec. 552). “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior, “Mineral leasing laws” shall mean the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1914-10-20"},"text":"October 20, 1914","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/741"},"text":"38 Stat. 741","children":[],"tail":", 48 U.S.C., sec. 432); the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1920-02-25"},"text":"February 25, 1920","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/437"},"text":"41 Stat. 437","children":[],"tail":", 30 U.S.C., sec. 181); the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1926-04-17"},"text":"April 17, 1926","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/301"},"text":"44 Stat. 301","children":[],"tail":", 30 U.S.C., sec. 271); the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1927-02-07"},"text":"February 7, 1927","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/1057"},"text":"44 Stat. 1057","children":[],"tail":", 30 U.S.C., sec. 281), and all Acts heretofore or hereafter enacted which are amendatory of or supplementary to 